et" data-widget_type=3D"heading.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<h2 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">What do a=
 kilowatt-hour and a watt-hour mean?</h2>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-6c218da elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"6c218da" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">A </span><b>kilowatt hour</b>=
<span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> (kWh), is a measurement of energy. When =
discussing energy usage in appliances within a household, 1 kWh refers to a=
 1-kilowatt (kW) appliance consuming energy for 1 hour. Another way kWh is =
used is to indicate the capacity of a battery bank, which we should conside=
r when deciding what batteries to purchase.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;=
</p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">A </span><b>watt-hour</b><span sty=
le=3D"font-weight: 400;"> (Wh) is simply a smaller version of the kilowatt-=
hour. 1 Wh is the amount of energy consumed by running a 1-watt (W) device =
in an hour.&nbsp;</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400=
;">Kilowatt-hours and watt-hours are both measurements of energy, and they =
are related units. The only difference is that one is much larger than the =
other. The conversion formula is:</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i><span style=
=3D"font-weight: 400;">1 kWh =3D 1,000 watt-hours</span></i></p>								</d=
iv>
				</div>
				</div>
					</div>
				</div>
		<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-7adb606 e-flex e-con-bo=
xed e-con e-parent" data-id=3D"7adb606" data-element_type=3D"container">
					<div class=3D"e-con-inner">
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-d0f5fb8 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-heading" data-id=3D"d0f5fb8" data-element_type=3D"widg=
et" data-widget_type=3D"heading.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<h2 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">How do yo=
u convert from kilowatt-hours (kWh) to kilowatts (kW)?</h2>				</div>
				</div>
					</div>
				</div>
		<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-682a213 e-flex e-con-bo=
xed e-con e-parent" data-id=3D"682a213" data-element_type=3D"container">
